pslib
------------------------------------------
pslib is a C-library to create PostScript files on the fly. It offers many
drawing primitives, inclusion of png and eps images and a very sophisticated
text rendering including hyphenation, kerning and ligatures. It can read
external Type1 fonts and embed them into the output file. It supports pdfmarks
which makes it in combination with ghostscript's pdfwriter an alternative for
libraries creating PDF.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.4-1
  libghthash1-0.6.2-1bl8
  libgif7-5.2.2-1
  libjpeg8-3.0.3-1
  libpng16-1.6.42-1
  libps-devel-0.4.8-1bl1
  libps0-0.4.8-1bl1
  libtiff7-4.6.0-1
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libghthash-devel-0.6.2-1bl8
  libgif-devel-5.2.2-1
  libjpeg-devel-3.0.3-1
  libpng-devel-1.6.42-1
  libtiff-devel-4.6.0-1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/pslib/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/pslib/pslib-0.4.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack pslib-0.4.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./pslib-0.4.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/pslib-0.4.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/pslib-0.4.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libps0-0.4.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libps-devel-0.4.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(pslib)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/pslib.README
  /usr/share/doc/pslib/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/pslib/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/pslib/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/pslib/README

(libps0)
  /usr/bin/cygps-0.dll
  /usr/share/locale/de/LC_MESSAGES/pslib.mo

(libps-devel)
  /usr/include/libps/pslib-mp.h
  /usr/include/libps/pslib.h
  /usr/include/libps/psversion.h
  /usr/lib/libps.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libps.pc
  /usr/share/pslib/draft.ps
  /usr/share/pslib/exectime.ps
  /usr/share/pslib/grid.ps

